"title": "5606: warfare, nature of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5606: warfare, nature of",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Warfare is characteristic of a fallen world. Scripture describes how some wars are justified and others are not.</p>\n<h2>Warfare is characteristic of a fallen world</h2>\n<h3>It is an aspect of life in a fallen world</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod17:16\">EXO 17:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam3:1\">2SA 3:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs14:30\">1KI 14:30</a></p>\n<h3>It is caused by sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas4:1-Jas4:2\">JAS 4:1–4:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps140:1-Ps140:2\">PSA 140:1–140:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov10:12\">PRO 10:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov29:22\">PRO 29:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor3:3\">1CO 3:3</a></p>\n<h3>It is horrific in nature</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Nah3:3\">NAM 3:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr25:12\">2CH 25:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech14:2\">ZEC 14:2</a></p>\n<h2>Warfare as a sign of the end times</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:6-Matt24:7\">MAT 24:6–24:7</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:7-Mark13:8\">MRK 13:7–13:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke21:9-Luke21:10\">LUK 21:9–21:10</a></p>\n<h2>Sometimes God forbids war</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut1:41-Deut1:42\">DEU 1:41–1:42</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs12:24\">1KI 12:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr22:8\">1CH 22:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps68:30\">PSA 68:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps120:7\">PSA 120:7</a></p>\n<h2>Sometimes God commands war</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh8:1\">JOS 8:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num31:7\">NUM 31:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut20:1-Deut20:4\">DEU 20:1–20:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh10:40\">JOS 10:40</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg6:16\">JDG 6:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps144:1\">PSA 144:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa13:3-Isa13:4\">ISA 13:3–13:4</a></p>\n<h2>Warfare is sometimes a means of judgment</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam15:2\">1SA 15:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs21:10-2Kgs21:15\">2KI 21:10–21:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs24:2-2Kgs24:4\">2KI 24:2–24:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa10:12-Isa10:19\">ISA 10:12–10:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer4:14-Jer4:18\">JER 4:14–4:18</a></p>\n<h2>God's will that warfare will finally cease</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps46:9\">PSA 46:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa2:4\">ISA 2:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic4:3\">MIC 4:3</a></p>",
